webpackJsonp([24780226909333],{720:function(e,a){e.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<p>Every cyclist who has ever gone uphill knows it is all about power to weight ratio. You can find your power to weight on strava if you look at your fitness chart and it only tells you what it is today. We track power and weight so you can see how they change over time and plot it to a graph for easy reference.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>\n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; margin: 0.4em auto; max-width: 412px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 70.04160887656033%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Power and Weight Charts"\n        title=""\n        src="/blog/static/power-and-weight-cover-e401d4b6fea8911816a964cda1169cf4-31818.png"\n        srcset="/blog/static/power-and-weight-cover-e401d4b6fea8911816a964cda1169cf4-b3e18.png 103w,\n/blog/static/power-and-weight-cover-e401d4b6fea8911816a964cda1169cf4-571c4.png 206w,\n/blog/static/power-and-weight-cover-e401d4b6fea8911816a964cda1169cf4-31818.png 412w,\n/blog/static/power-and-weight-cover-e401d4b6fea8911816a964cda1169cf4-1be92.png 618w,\n/blog/static/power-and-weight-cover-e401d4b6fea8911816a964cda1169cf4-05b5b.png 824w,\n/blog/static/power-and-weight-cover-e401d4b6fea8911816a964cda1169cf4-17809.png 1236w,\n/blog/static/power-and-weight-cover-e401d4b6fea8911816a964cda1169cf4-27003.png 1442w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 412px) 100vw, 412px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  </p>\n<p>When it comes to Climbing, it is all about Power and Weight, and well, Endurance, but this page focuses on Power and Weight.</p>\n<p>At this time, Strava lets you enter your current FTP (<a href="https://www.strava.com/settings/performance" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">here</a>) and Weight (<a href="https://www.strava.com/settings/profile" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">here</a>), but it only keeps this as a single value and does not save a history. Update your Strava numbers as necessary and A Race athlete will keep track of this for you on this page.\nWe will also calculate and track your Watts per Kilogram while we are at it.</p>\n<p>If you would like to focus in on a smaller range of data, use the slider below the charts.</p>',frontmatter:{title:"Power and Weight",date:"2017-06-05T00:19:00.000Z",path:"/power-and-weight/",parent:"/home/hypersprite/Documents/code/araceathlete-gatsby-material-ui-v1/src/pages/blog-posts/power-and-weight.md absPath of file",tags:"newbie,power,weight",description:"Track Watts per Kilogram with Power and Weight",cover:{childImageSharp:{responsiveSizes:{src:"/blog/static/power-and-weight-cover-e401d4b6fea8911816a964cda1169cf4-7b166.png",sizes:"(max-width: 412px) 100vw, 412px",srcSet:"/blog/static/power-and-weight-cover-e401d4b6fea8911816a964cda1169cf4-32196.png 103w,\n/blog/static/power-and-weight-cover-e401d4b6fea8911816a964cda1169cf4-e3336.png 206w,\n/blog/static/power-and-weight-cover-e401d4b6fea8911816a964cda1169cf4-7b166.png 412w,\n/blog/static/power-and-weight-cover-e401d4b6fea8911816a964cda1169cf4-01e4b.png 618w,\n/blog/static/power-and-weight-cover-e401d4b6fea8911816a964cda1169cf4-0751a.png 824w,\n/blog/static/power-and-weight-cover-e401d4b6fea8911816a964cda1169cf4-832e5.png 1236w,\n/blog/static/power-and-weight-cover-e401d4b6fea8911816a964cda1169cf4-d700e.png 1442w",originalImg:"/blog/static/power-and-weight-cover-e401d4b6fea8911816a964cda1169cf4-d700e.png",originalName:"power-and-weight-cover.png",aspectRatio:1.4277227722772277,base64:"data:image/png;base64,"}}}}}},pathContext:{slug:"/blog-posts/power-and-weight/"}}}});
